[SN]TITLE[SN]
£160k to help brain injury patients cook for themselves at home

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A £160,000 fund will be used to help people suffering from brain injuries cook for themselves at home.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Betsi Cadwaladr University Health Board is searching for "innovative cooking solutions" to help those who use the North Wales Brain Injury Service.
Businesses will work with the health board over two years to find ways to increase people's independence at home.
Dr Rudi Coetzer said: "It is an opportunity to find solutions to daily frustrations our service users face."
